gomodel:SYNGO_3675  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Studying excitatory hippocampal synapses, Fig. 2 shows that mEPSC amplitude is reduced upon neurexin-3ab deletion in neurons cultured from the hippocampus. Using cultured KO neurons, Fig. 3 shows that presynaptic neurexin-3ab deletion caused a selective trans-synaptic downregulation of postsynaptic AMPA-type glutamate receptors. Fig. 5 supports that presynaptic deletion of neurexin-3ab in vivo at CA1-subiculum synapses impairs postsynaptic AMPAR-mediated responses. No change in presynaptic release was observed.. Experimental description: Conditional KO mice were studied" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3675" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
